ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: in past month: description of traumatic event
directly experiencing the traumatic events, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: witnessing, in person, the event(s) as it occurred to others, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: learning that the traumatic event(s) occurred to a close family member or close friend. In cases of actual or threatened death of a family member or friend, the event(s) must have been violent or accidental, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: experiencing repeated or extreme exposure to aversive details of the traumatic event(s), past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: at least one A item coded "3", past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: recurrent, involuntary, and intrusive distressing memories of the traumatic event(s), past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: recurrent distressing dreams in which the content and/or affect of the dream are related to the traumatic event, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: dissociative reactions in which the individual feels or acts as if the traumatic event(s) were recurring., past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: intense or prolong psychological distress at exposure to internal or external cues that symbolize or resemble an aspect of the traumatic event, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: persistent inability to experience positive emotions, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: past month, an altered sense of one's surrounding or one's self
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: inability to remember an important aspect of the traumatic event(s), past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: efforts to avoid distressing memories, thoughts, or feelings about or closely related with traumatic events, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: efforts to avoid external reminders (people, places, conversations, activities, objects, situations) that arouse distressing memories, thoughts, or feelings about or closely associated with traumatic events, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: sleep disturbances (e.g. difficulty falling or stayling asleep or restless sleep), past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: irritable behavior and angry outbursts, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: hypervigilance, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: problems with concentration, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: exaggerated startle response, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: at least nine B items coded "3", past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported

ElementDescription: duration of the disturbance is 3 days to 1 month after trauma exposure, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 2 = subthreshold; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: disturbance causes clinically significant distress or impairment in social, occupational, or other important areas of functioning, past month
Notes: 1= Absent or False; 2= Subthreshold; 3= Threshold or True; 4= Mild; 5= Moderate; 6= Severe; -7= N/A; -9= Missing or Not Reported; -1= Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: disturbance is not attriubtable to the physiological effects of a substance or another medical condition, past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported; -1 = Inadequate Information/Unknown

ElementDescription: Acute Stress Disorder Criteria A, B, C, D, and E are coded "3", past month
Notes: 1= absent or false; 3 = threshold or true; -7 = N/A; -9 = missing or not reported
